Between 2003 and 2008, a total of 2795 FBDOs were reported, which resulted in 62559 illnesses, 31261 hospitalizations, and 330 deaths (Table 1
). Reports of outbreaks peaked in 2003 (772 outbreaks), falling to 262 outbreaks in 2008, with an average annual number of 466. The average annual rate of outbreaks and cases was 0.8 and 18.4 per 1 million population, respectively. Outbreaks are markedly seasonal, peaking in warmer months (Fig. 1
). The seasonal trend of microbial outbreaks was similar to that of FBDOs, but other causes of outbreaks did not have such seasonal trend.
